Subject: [PATCH 1/3] fix(mcp): route /api/mcp/servers + /api/mcp/reload
 through dashboardFetch

Zero-fork architecture: Hermes gateway (:8642) only serves /health,
/v1/chat/completions, /v1/models. The config API lives on the dashboard
(:9119) and requires the session token that dashboardFetch() already
handles. The previous code called fetch(`${HERMES_API}/api/config`) and
surfaced `Failed to load MCP servers from gateway config (404).` on the
/mcp page.

- servers.ts: swap direct gateway fetch for dashboardFetch(/api/config);
  drop unused BEARER_TOKEN/authHeaders imports; update error message to
  say "dashboard" instead of "gateway". Keep the existing capability
  fallback so older enhanced-fork backends still work.
- reload.ts: probe the dashboard first when caps.dashboard.available,
  then fall through to the gateway reload paths for enhanced-fork
  backends.
---
 src/routes/api/mcp/reload.ts  | 32 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 src/routes/api/mcp/servers.ts | 20 ++++++++------------
 2 files changed, 39 insertions(+), 13 deletions(-)

